    <div class="twothird">
      <h1>Public Policy</h1>
      <h5 class="padding-32">Between my B.A. in Astronomy/Physics (Univeristy of Virginia 2013) and starting my Ph.D., I earned a Master of Public Policy (MPP) degree from the <a href="http://batten.virginia.edu/">Frank Batten School of Leadership & Public Policy at the University of Virginia</a>. Through the program, I learned and practiced many general policy skills, including writing breifs, memos, and other articles as well as analyzing the effectiveness of policies. I applied these lessons in my internship with the <a href="http://www.aapt.org/">American Association of Physics Teachers (AAPT)</a> where I created advocacy resources to enourage and aid members in interacting with policymakers. For my MPP thesis, I wrote a policy analysis with AAPT on increasing gender diversity in physics, and I presented the results at the 5th International Conference on Women in Physics in Waterloo, Canada. </h5>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Third Grid -->
<div class="row-padding padding-64 container">
  <div class="content">
    <!--div class="twothird"-->
    <div>
      <h1>Outreach & Teaching</h1>
      <h5 class="padding-32">I've also pursued opportunities to teach and conduct outreach. Most recently, I volunteered with the <a href="http://warrior-scholar.org/">Warrior Scholar Project</a>, an academic "bootcamp" for veterans returning to school, during their STEM week at the University of Arizona. I co-led a daily exoplanet research lab and provided additional instructional assistance during recitation sections.</h5>

      <h5>In Spring 2017, I was the TA for an introductory astronomy course for non-majors that was taught in a planetarium theatre. I volunteered to give one of the lectures (Milky Way structure) and developed a lecture combining a traditional slideshow with planetarium software features. In the past, I have TA-ed for introductory physics courses, and while I was getting my MPP, I TA-ed for an economics course and tutored statistics (including statistical programming in STATA).</h5>
    </div>

    <!--div class="third center">
      <img class="img-circle" src="./images/pic03.jpg">
    </div-->
  </div>
</div>

